-- 7. Tonbridge × Digital Marketing
INSERT INTO public.local_content (service_slug, town_slug, intro_paragraph, local_context, competition_landscape, success_approach, local_stats, pain_points, solutions, faqs, layout_variant)
VALUES (
  'digital-marketing',
  'tonbridge',
  'Tonbridge''s population of 39,000 sits within the larger Tonbridge and Malling borough, creating a substantial addressable market for businesses that know how to reach it digitally. The town''s commuter demographic researches everything online. The family demographic compares and reviews before choosing. The business community networks through digital channels. Yet most Tonbridge businesses rely on High Street footfall and word of mouth alone, leaving significant revenue on the table. Digital marketing reaches the customers who do not walk past your door: the commuter who searches on the train, the family in the outer borough who has never visited the Castle area, the new resident who has no existing service providers. We build focused digital marketing campaigns for Tonbridge businesses that generate measurable enquiries and revenue from precisely targeted local audiences.',
  'Tonbridge''s digital marketing landscape offers multiple channels for reaching distinct audiences. Google Search captures high-intent service queries from across the borough. Facebook advertising reaches the family demographic affordably, leveraging the active community group culture. LinkedIn targeting connects professional services with the commuter demographic. Instagram advertising drives discovery for hospitality, retail, and lifestyle businesses, with Tonbridge Castle and the River Medway providing strong visual advertising hooks. The borough context means campaigns can target broader geographic areas while maintaining local relevance.',
  'Digital marketing competition in Tonbridge is moderate. Google Ads costs for Tonbridge keywords are reasonable compared to London but rising as more businesses invest. Facebook advertising remains affordable for reaching the local demographic. A small number of Tonbridge businesses run consistent digital campaigns and capture disproportionate market share. The majority still rely on organic reach alone, creating opportunity for businesses willing to invest strategically.',
  'We build Tonbridge digital marketing campaigns focused on return rather than activity. Every campaign targets the specific postcodes, demographics, and behaviours that define your ideal customer. We test channels on controlled budgets, identify what converts, and scale the winners. Monthly reporting shows exactly what your investment produced in enquiries and revenue, not impressions or clicks that do not translate to business.',
  '{"population": 39000, "borough": "Tonbridge and Malling", "commute_time": "28 minutes to London", "business_districts": ["High Street", "Castle area", "Hadlow Road", "Quarry Hill area"], "key_fact": "Borough-wide addressable market accessible through precisely targeted digital campaigns"}',
  '[{"title": "High Street reliance limiting Tonbridge business growth", "description": "Footfall and word of mouth reach the customers who already know you or walk past your door. They cannot reach the commuter who searches on the train, the family in the outer borough, or the new resident who has no established service providers. Digital marketing breaks through the geographic ceiling that physical presence imposes."}, {"title": "Untargeted campaigns wasting Tonbridge marketing budgets", "description": "Boosting Facebook posts or running broad Google Ads without geographic and demographic targeting wastes budget on people who will never become customers. Tonbridge businesses need campaigns that reach specific postcodes, age groups, and interest profiles relevant to their actual service offering."}, {"title": "No attribution connecting Tonbridge marketing to revenue", "description": "Many Tonbridge businesses spend money on marketing without knowing what works. A Facebook ad here, a Google listing there, a print advertisement somewhere else. Without tracking and attribution, budget flows to habit rather than results. Digital marketing with proper measurement fixes this entirely."}]',
  '[{"title": "Borough-targeted Google Ads for Tonbridge searches", "description": "Google Ads campaigns targeting the specific search terms Tonbridge and Malling residents use for your services. Geographic targeting focuses budget on relevant postcodes. Local ad copy improves click-through rates. Landing pages convert clicks into enquiries. Every pound tracks to a measurable outcome."}, {"title": "Multi-channel campaigns reaching Tonbridge''s diverse demographics", "description": "Facebook advertising for families and community engagement. LinkedIn for professional services and the commuter demographic. Instagram for visual discovery and hospitality. Google for active search capture. We build campaigns across the channels your Tonbridge audience uses, with each platform optimised for its specific strength."}, {"title": "Revenue-attributed reporting for Tonbridge business decisions", "description": "Monthly reports showing enquiries generated, cost per lead, and revenue attributable to each campaign and channel. No vanity metrics. Tonbridge business owners see exactly what their marketing investment produces, with clear recommendations for budget allocation based on proven performance."}]',
  '[{"question": "What budget does a Tonbridge business need for digital marketing?", "answer": "Effective campaigns in Tonbridge typically start from seven hundred to fifteen hundred pounds monthly in ad spend plus management. Google Ads costs are reasonable for most Tonbridge keywords. We always recommend starting focused, proving results, and scaling based on demonstrated return on investment."}, {"question": "Which channels work best for Tonbridge businesses?", "answer": "Google Ads performs consistently for service searches. Facebook reaches families and the community effectively. LinkedIn targets the professional commuter demographic precisely. Instagram drives discovery for hospitality and retail. We test the mix for your specific business rather than applying a generic formula."}, {"question": "How quickly will I see results from digital marketing?", "answer": "Google Ads can generate enquiries from day one. Facebook and social campaigns typically build momentum over two to three weeks. Most Tonbridge clients achieve a positive return on investment within the first month, with results improving as campaigns optimise through the first quarter."}, {"question": "Can you target specific areas within the Tonbridge and Malling borough?", "answer": "Yes. We can target campaigns at specific postcodes, towns, and areas within the borough. Whether you want to reach Tonbridge town centre, the surrounding villages, or the wider Malling area, geographic precision ensures your budget reaches the customers most likely to use your services."}]',
  'lead-gen'
)
